data:
{"caption":"India's Protein Crisis: 70% of popular supplements failed the lab test. 🧪 Is your 'health' drink actually toxic? 

New research reveals heavy metals, pesticides, and fungal toxins in the tubs you trust. Stop being a lab rat for big brands. Watch till the end to know how to stay safe.

#IndianFitness #ProteinScam #HealthAlert #GymMotivation #Supplements #FitnessIndia #Exposed #WaitForKey #HealthAwareness","format":"Reel/Short","hashtags":["#IndianFitness","#ProteinScam","#GymControversy","#HealthAlert","#SupplementsIndia","#FitnessFacts","#HeavyMetals","#NutritionWaste","#WorkoutMotivation","#Exposed"],"niche":"Fitness/Health Controversy","script":{"dialogue":"Kya aap jaante hain aapke protein bucket mein muscle ke saath saath zeher bhi ho sakta hai? Research mein pata chala hai ki India ke 70% popular protein supplements mislabeled hain. Sirf label hi nahi, 14% samples mein fungal toxins aur 8% mein harmful pesticides mile hain. Kuch brands mein toh lead aur arsenic jaise heavy metals bhi detect huye hain. Log sochte hain protein powder se liver damage hota hai, par sach toh ye hai ki ye nakli supplements aur pesticides aapka liver kharaab kar rahe hain. Har chamakti hui dabba quality nahi hoti. Supplement lene se pehle lab reports check kijiye aur blind trust band kijiye. Kyunki sehat banane chale the, kahin gawa na baitho.","suggestedElevenLabsVoice":{"name":"Antoni","voiceId":"exoL2Z47H69R4K2fmkZY"},"voiceDirection":"Serious, fast-paced, urgent, and warning. Use deep pauses for emphasis on 'zeher' and 'mislabeled'."},"sources":[{"claim":"70% of 36 popular protein supplements sold in India are mislabeled.","url":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DYSELlJB5vt/"},{"claim":"14% of tested protein samples had fungal toxins and 8% had pesticides.","url":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DZU_CKVFlgw/"},{"claim":"Reports of heavy metals like lead and arsenic found in Indian protein supplements.","url":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DZK9VHzPX-_/"}],"thumbnailPrompts":["Close-up of a protein scoop dripping with dark, oily sludge instead of powder. Large text: '70% FAKE PROTEIN?' with a warning sign. High contrast, gritty gym background.","A muscular man looking shocked at a lab report. In the background, protein tubs with 'TOXIC' stamps. Text: 'POISON IN YOUR PROTEIN'. Dramatic lighting.","Split screen: One side a shiny protein tub, other side a microscope view of bacteria and metal shards. Text: 'THE DARK TRUTH'. Neon red and white bold text."],"topic":"The Indian Protein Powder Scandal: Toxic Additives and Mislabeling","visuals":[{"beat":"0-3s hook","imagePrompt":"Ultra-realistic close-up of a black protein tub being opened, but green toxic gas emerges instead of powder. Cinematic lighting, dark gym aesthetic.","onScreenText":"70% PROTEIN IS FAKE?","videoPrompt":"Slow motion zoom into a protein tub as toxic neon green vapor swirls out. Camera shakes slightly for dramatic effect."},{"beat":"3-8s the data","imagePrompt":"Splitscreen graphic. Left: A lab technician holding a test tube. Right: A list of 'Heavy Metals' and 'Pesticides' appearing in bold red font. Professional lab setting.","onScreenText":"LAB REPORTS EXPOSED","videoPrompt":"Fast cuts between lab equipment, microscopes, and fitness enthusiasts drinking shakes with a 'glitch' effect overlay."},{"beat":"8-15s the danger","imagePrompt":"A cinematic shot of a human liver glowing with a red warning light inside a body. Dark background. Symbolizing internal damage.","onScreenText":"HEAVY METALS & PESTICIDES","videoPrompt":"3D medical animation showing toxic particles entering the bloodstream from a drink. Quick, aggressive camera movement."},{"beat":"15-22s the reality","imagePrompt":"Crowded Indian supplement shop with shelves full of neon-colored tubs, but they all have a 'Hazard' sticker on them. Gritty, street-style photography.","onScreenText":"DONT BLINDLY TRUST BRANDS","videoPrompt":"Panning shot across various supplement jars that slowly turn into skulls or warning signs as the camera passes."},{"beat":"22-30s call to action","imagePrompt":"A fitness influencer looking directly into the camera with a serious expression, holding a phone showing a lab report. Moody gym lighting.","onScreenText":"STAY SAFE. CHECK REPORTS.","videoPrompt":"Handheld camera stabilizes on the speaker’s face as the background blurs. Final fade to black with a 'Share this' icon."}],"whyViral":"This topic taps into the high-anxiety 'Health & Safety' niche. It challenges the 'health' status of products millions of Indians use daily. High-retention hooks ('Zeher' and '70% Fake') and evidence-based shock value are proven to trigger mass shares among gym-goers and parents."}
